    "created_at": "2016-11-03T02:51:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-11-03T02:51:33Z",
    "body": "I was about to open the same issue ðŸ˜¸ . I'm seeing it in 1.4.5 on macOS.\n\nFor anyone looking for a workaround, I've found that you can set the zoom on just the webview (e.g. `webview.setZoomFactor(1.1)`) but leave the zoom untouched in the parent renderer. If you have additional UI in the parent renderer and you want that zoomed as well, you can always use the CSS `zoom` property. Setting `zoom` on the body doesn't seem to affect the webview. \n"
  },
