    "created_at": "2017-06-07T01:55:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-06-07T01:55:25Z",
    "body": "Hi there @bpasero ,\r\n\r\nI have actually experienced the same issue and spent quite a while figuring this out. I'm not sure if you have by now, but just for a reference or anybody stumbling on this issue as well, the trick is to not set the height and width using percentage (or calc(_ ...) as I was using)_ but to use the vh and vw units.\r\n\r\n`<webview style=\"height: 100vh; width: 100vw\" ...`\r\n\r\nAdditionally, your html, body elements should be:\r\n\r\n`\r\nbody, html { height: 100%; width: 100%; min-height: 100%; min-width: 100% }\r\n`\r\n\r\n"
  },
